# Week 4 Keywords  
## 4.1 - An in vitro system for caspase activation
**[PARP](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poly_ADP_ribose_polymerase)**  
* poly(ADP-ribose) polymerase  
* Is cleaved  in apoptotic cells. 
* The amino acid sequence of one of the cleavage sites of PARP is similar to the amino acid sequence of one of the cleavage sites in interleukin-1beta, which is cleaved by ICE.  
* It is DEVD in the case of PARP and FEAD in the case of interleukin-1beta.  
* In both cases, cleavage occurs after the fourth amino acid, the aspartic acid residue.  
  
