**HeLa cells** 
* immortal human cell line. First human cell line isolated and most commonly used human cell line. 
* Derived in 1951 from a cervical cancer removed from a patient named [Henrietta Lacks](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henrietta_Lacks), who died of cancer that same year.  
  
